      <div class="msgContentFrame">at least for me.  seems the only reliable way ill skill up at rank 9 is by using copper-based stuff.  if i try anything bronze, even using the 2nd tier guild forge in LL, i fail more often than not.  shards arent easy to find, and i cant afford to blow nearly a dozen of them for 100 armorer points. <br /> <br />anyone else having this problem or is it just me?  ive tried altering what tool ive used, but the only reliable solution is to chip away at it with lower level copper synths, which is a long process, but at least more efficient per shard.  feels like they made some changes since beta.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">The thing about me is that apparently it's very hard to tell when I'm drunk. So I feel like I'm walking sideways on a UFO and everyone else sees me doing the robot like a pro.</div></div> - <b>MojoVIII</b> <br />i have bathed in the blood of many.  my life was spent well. <br />feral druids do it on all fours. <br />The One True Prophet of Tonkism. <br /> <br /><a href="http://therewillbebrawl.com/" title="http://therewillbebrawl.com/" rel="external nofollow">http://therewillbebrawl.com/</a></div></div>
