      <div class="msgContentFrame">It gets better.  Once you get to around 14-15 you can start making wire.  (Guild support recommended).  One synth = 12 wire.  Take each of those twelve wires and break them down into bronze rings.  Take six of those bronze rings and convert it to bronze chain. Convert 2 chain and 1 wire into a bronze chainmail vest (it's a component, not yet a wearable piece).  Convert another 1 chain and 1 wire into bronze chainmail sleeves.  Set aside. <br /> <br />You'd have to poke around for the rest of the mats, but right there is the lion's share of the armorer-supplied materials for bronze chainmail, sentinel's chainmail,and bronze haubergeon. <br /> <br />Around 15-20 armorer is when you really start to feel like an armorer.  Not only do you get to make the bits that everyone so badly wants right now, but the process of making the gear from start to finish is very involved.  That might seem daunting to some, but when you think of it in terms of class xp you're earning with each stage of the production, 15+ cruises by at a pretty healthy clip.  I just hit rank 18 tonight and succeeded at 3 out of 4 attempts at bronze haubergeons (all three now sitting in my bazaar for the rock bottom price of 75k each.)  Lots of fun.</div>
