      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Kilnaga wrote:</div><div class="orig">So you extremely undercut and made next to no profit? The NPC cost of materials to make a Bronze Hauby is just north of 60k.</div></div> <br /> <br />I don't buy materials from NPC.  I make my own cloth, my own leather straps, my own brass buckles (from my own homemade brass nuggets), and my own chain components from scratch.  All I spend any gil on at all are shards because I make make the gil to buy the shards faster than I can farm them.  Everything else I need I have in abundance. <br /> <br />The NPC prices on materials beyond about the rank 7-10 range of synthesis items are grossly and purposefully inflated by SE.  They aren't intending for players to rely on them as the game ages, and the prices are intended to reflect that.  It's the same as it was in FFXI.  Nobody in their right mind would by more than copper or tin ore from the NPC vendors in FFXI because everything after that was vastly overpriced compared to the common auction value (excluding RMT hyper-inflation, of course). <br /> <br />I think people from XI see &quot;haubergeon&quot; in the name of an item and go all batsh*t crazy for it.  In reality, it's not that good.  It's a fine piece of armor for what it is...a transitional piece from late mid-game until current level capped gear.  People using a bronze haubergeon now (are crazy, first of all, but I digress) are going to be seeing use out of it for some time to come.  And then they're quite possibly going to be plunking it in storage or selling it when they get something better.  Every server right now is experiencing a period of significant inflation because demand is through the roof and supply is through the floor. <br /> <br />Every armorer and their dog is clawing their way up to the point where they can make bronze haubergeons and other related goodies because it's solid bank (and with all the components from ingots -&gt; wire -&gt; rings -&gt; sheets -&gt; final sub-components, it's insane skill points to boot.)  Eventually, those who want a haubergeon will have one, or enough crafters will be making the next step up that the bronze bits become old news.  At that point, the value of them is going to tank.  I don't need to capitalize excessively on the current situation in order to turn a profit.  By the end of the week, I'll have well over 1 million gil in my treasury and the means to make plenty more.  If I can make and repair my own gear, that means I don't even really need the gil. I can gather my own mats, buy shards, and continue to make gil from now until the focused crafters outstrip the people like me who try to do a bit of everything.  At which points, I'll still have my million+ gil and the means to make and repair my own gear.  Win.</div>
